-- FinMin expects robust pickup in Germany next year
-- 
-- Mon May 16, 2011 8:12am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/05/16/us-eurozone-germany-schaeuble-idUSTRE74F1HE20110516

 

 BERLIN  (Reuters) - Germany's Finance Minister Wolfgang Schaeuble expects a robust pickup in the Europe's largest economy next year as well, he said on Monday. 

 Schaeuble also said defending the stability of the euro is a difficult policy but is in the interests of Germany's economy. (Reporting by Andreas Kroener; Writing by  Sam Cage )